caption: Wow.. amazing food with so much flavor.
Great service, nice staff and food is GREAT! Highly recommended!
Amazing food and service

We've been many times and the owner is a parent at our son's school (he's a really nice guy).  Anyway, this was our first indoor meal since the pandemic began 12 months ago. I couldn't think of a nicer way to celebrate my birthday.  I honestly don't think you can go wrong on their menu - the salads,  tacos, and mains are all fantastic. My only regret is not trying dessert, as I had birthday cake waiting for me at home...
Great food and atmosphere for a first date.

I went last night with my mother because she’s staying down the street at the holiday inn and we wanted to grab a bite in the neighborhood. On first arrival it’s very homey and comfortable, like if you needed somewhere warm to sit after a long journey this is where I’d come.  My mom and I just shared a few plates, the quesadilla, kale salad and then the fried chicken with yucca. All of them were delicious and filling. Quesadilla is an appetizer but pretty big for the portion. Fried chicken was tasty and perfectly crisped.  Got the strawberry crisp for dessert and was 100% satisfied with my choice. The waiter gave me his recommendation and I was very happy about it. He was also very kind I wish I got his name he was so sweet!!!
Delicious food and cozy outdoor environment with heat lamps and wood burning fire pit!

Palo Santo is an awesome spot to have in the neighborhood! It's unpretentious and unique with some really delicious options.  We went for NYE and got the prix fixe which was really substantial and super affordable.  The waiter definitely got slammed with takeout orders and tables, but we still felt like the service was friendly and the food was really tasty.  Definitely a cute and vibey spot that doesn't feel overrun by trend-seekers.
Great flavors, totally fun menu right now for takeout as well
Great food great service love it!

I recommend making a reservation for brunch if you have 6 people or more. Luckily we only waited for 10 mins. They have tables outside on the sidewalk and the courtyard. A couple of tables inside. If you use a credit card, there's a small fee (stated on the menu), which I'm surprised to see.  So it's $21 for all the brunch dishes, which comes with a choice of non alcoholic drinks. I ordered the pupusa dish and it was really good, but it was small. They give you two palm size pieces with beans, guacamole, and slaw. I was still hungry afterwards. My friends that ordered the egg dishes are filling. Another friend ordered the french toast and it was pretty big, but her husband got the fish and grits and that was really small. Also doesn't seem like there's a free refill for coffee since they never offered. So the conclusion is that my dish wasn't worth it, since I had to go somewhere else to fill up my poor stomach.

Our close friends are local and avid lovers of this spot, so naturally, it was our turn to join on their adventure. The owner is a gifted artisanal chef. His menu changes often and the offers are so impressive. He knows how to balance flavors with unique twists. We nearly ordered every appetizer on the menu, along with a pitcher of sangria. The entrees were delicious - the tuna entree substituted for swordfish was flavorful, the crispy chicken-styled entree was a high end twist to batter wings and the plantain coconut dish (first on the entree menu) was impressive in presentation - literally in a coconut shell- and in its flavor. I know I butchered the names on the menu... nevertheless, you cannot go wrong with ordering anything here. The friendly ambiance will nurture your food baby to good health by the time you leave. 5+ stars.
The food is fabulous,  environment cozy.
Quality latin food and very warm service.

Brunch was AMAZING. I added the bottomless booze. We had the coconut pancakes, fish tacos and steak and eggs. All were delicious and seasoned to perfection. Full of flavor and quality ingredients. I do wish the fish tacos were bigger, or at least had an additional side with it. Service was good and polite. Loved it

The food was so delicious. We had the patty pan squash appetizer (so complex and rich), the fish tacos (derp fried fish to perfection) and the Berkshire pork which was perfectly cooked and so flavorful, highly, highly recommend.

If you’ve never dined at Palo Santo, treat yourself today. It’s a 5-star experience, everything from the quality and originality of the food, to the genuine hospitality, and the charming location.  But, bring your appetite — the menu might seem like another “small plate” prix fixe experience, but you’ll leave incredibly satisfied.

Very cute, brownstone with a spacious back area. The food was excellent. The drinks were excellent (especially the sangria)! If you enjoy many different genres of music with a dancing beat you'll definitely love this place.
Lovely food and great outdoor dining

(Translated by Google) The servers are very friendly, they speak Spanish in case you are a tourist, very delicious food  (Original) Los meseros son muy amables , hablan español  por si eres turista , comida muy rica
food is fresh and organic  and the vibe is great the people are great

This tiny restaurant on the first floor of a brownstone (res recommended) offers fantastic cuisine with a Latin American twist. Great happy hour. Perfect for a casual weeknight or relaxed weekend dinner - try the duck. #vero #travel #brooklyn #restaurant
Great service and food

You can close your eyes and point at ANY ITEM ON THE MENU - DELICIOUS. if you are vegetarian there will be some options (YAM - I am). None for vegan. All that cheese you know... Beers, wines and mimosas. ALSO bottomless mimosas for $15 on weekends till 3pm. Best spot.
Great covid dining spot
GreEat
Perfection. Some of the best food in Brooklyn, hands down.
Amazing food and great service

Such great food. Blown away by the coconut plantain stew. The quesadilla was phenomenal.  Insane value, actually. Fine dining quality food, and for only 30 dollars a pop. We got the prix fixe dinner for 2 - quarantine date - night - and were so happy with our meal. We even had enough for tomorrows'lunch - so don't worry about the portion. Honestly, I have no idea why they are charging so little. That could have easily been 100 dollars and would be totally reasonable even at that price.  Thank you for staying open during the pandemic, I truly appreciate it. Very friendly staff, and the food is an easy 5/5.
Yay
Went here for brunch it was amazing
Cozy place. Lovely service.
Cozy and intimate. Expensive, but delicious

Often brunch is good, but kind of a letdown. This brunch, on the other hand, was delicious and offered unique Pan-Latin dishes. We did the bottomless mimosas and sangria with friends and never felt rushed by our waitress. Great service and delicious food in a cozy space.

We came here to celebrate my MIL's birthday.  The ambience in the back was nice until more people started coming in.  It became quite loud and difficult to keep a conversation between the 9 of us.  Also, it was a bit cold in the back, my kids didn't take their coats off.  The food was very slow to come, small portions, but tated good but nothing amazing, so be sure to plan accordingly if you are really hungry.  Typically with outings like this we end up bringing food home but this time there wasn't one morsel left.  I'd be on the fence about coming back here again.  Perhaps in a much smaller party.
Amazing food and terrific staff. Highly recommend the platano stuffed with beef, the quesadillas and the poblano tortilla soup! The bread pudding is cravable ...and alone worth the trip.
Atmosphere was great. Very cozy. But the food was bland and overcompensated for by grease and cheese.

Food was phenomenal. Been wanting to come here for years and I'm glad I did! The drinks were especially delicious and creative too! Very clean service area. Wait staff were accommodating and attentive but not overbearing which is a hard balance to maintain and they executed their duties perfectly! Would definitely return  Not a good place to go when it's cold outside since it's very drafty and we were seated literally next to the door so every time it opened, I got blasted by the cold. It honestly isn't a good place to put a table... at least in the winter

Not far from heaven  One might think you died when you're here. It is too good to be true. $31 for brunch and bottomless mimosas? This isnt Witchita, NB, this is NYC. And they dont dilute the mimosa with OJ. These are proper drinks. Food is amazing and the space is super chill. I'm about to be a local and I live 30 minutes away.
Great brunch spot with a south of the border twist.  I want to return in a few months to enjoy the patio.

Went to Palo Santo last night for a New Years dinner. Arrived hungry around 9:00 pm, left hungry shortly after 12:00 am. Ended up paying around $150 for dinner and portions were laughably small, to the point it felt like a slap in the face. We kept wondering when we’d be receiving anything at all resembling a decent portion, as depicted on the restaurant’s website - sadly, it never came. I’ve done tasting menus before, and never have I left this hungry or this unsatisfied.

Great food but a little pricey and small portions
Gave us a lot of drinks. Good people.
Great food! Great staff!

Had my baby shower in the private room last week. Everything was phenomenal. The staff were so accommodating and even the guests commented on how nice everyone was. Gonzalo is a sweetheart and always willing to help. Everyone also commented on how yummy the food was. Highly recommend the back room for any event where you have between 25-35 guests. (I had 28 guests and was still able to set up my big dessert table by the window where I wanted)
Great food!
Tasty food, great service, relaxing environment
really wonderful spot. The outdoor seating is lovely. And the Coconut Jackfruit Stew is divine, as is a corn soup I tried. Also, marvelous deserts.

Palo Santo has a innovative menu, that has been delicious and high-quality each time I have been for dinner. It has a warm, peaceful atmosphere. It could be great for a romantic date or small family meal. The restaurant is small, and has a cute yet tiny front patio.
Amazing food and service! Also nice vibes (specially the backyard)!
Great food, excellent service. They have a nice outdoor patio. Inside is rustic and casual. They even gave us complementary chocolate cake!

Super nice reourpised house the middle of a housing block now serving as Latin restaurant. Dominican influences, Mexican. But unlike many other fusion type restaurants this is done very (very) proper. Limited menu that seems to rotate frequently. Shared a dish with pulled beef in a charred plantain with rice and beans and a water melon salad. Great service. I'd come back.

Customer service is good but the food is extremely disappointing. Will not return there again. For a spanish place to serve spanish food with no flavor is not spanish no more. They need to improve the Menu and pricing as well.
Food was delicious, best nopales tacos I ever had. Price is a but high but justified by the quality of the food. Restaurant also has a cozy ambience, specially the cute little garden in the back.

The place is amazing for large parties. We had our wedding in the back room and it was perfect. The service was above and beyond , they handed guest drinks as they came in and kept the drinks coming all night long. The food was beyond, and they even made a plate for our photographer. The atmosphere  is great and they even allow access to the backyard which was great for photos. 100% a hidden gem!
Came for brunch and enjoyed the chilaquiles and a michelada. Very nice service, and their homemade scotch bonnet hot sauce was amazing!

Fun place with slow but amazingly friendly and thoughtful service. We came here for a bachelorette brunch on a Saturday and they were gracious and flexible when we had two people not show up for our larger reservation. We ordered a bunch of drinks including coffee (decent), mimosas (pretty good) as well as a nice array of their brunch items such as the french toast (fluffy and sweet), the pork hash and eggs (delicious -- the slaw added a real freshness to the fatty, gooey dish), and the chilaquiles (yummy but could be spicier). Since our entrees took a good while to come out, they also offered us a champagne toast, an avocado ceviche on the house, and several desserts to round out the meal. Come here and expect awesome service, and although you might be waiting a while for your actual food it's such a fun and delicious time you probably won't notice!  (Value is great as well: $200 post tax and tip for 7 people with entrees and multiple drinks.)
Really nice spot for a cozy dinner.

Great food, really nice staff.  I love to sit at the bar - you can see the chefs cooking and the heat from the kitchen doesn't really affect you.  There's not really anything bad on the menu except for the stew that comes in far too small of a portion for what you pay for.  It's so simple but delicious, get the avocado and fresh tortillas - they are simply amazing.  During the summer they'll occasionally have spicy sangria.  I love it!

It’s literally in a brownstone basement unit. It’s such a cool setting.  We had brunch; all four of us had different dishes. A few had the prix fixe menu.  The coffee is surprisingly good. It came with steamed whole milk and raw sugar on the side.  The dishes themselves were all a hit. My wife had the egg sandwich and I had the Chilaquiles de Pollo. Both were amazing.
Reliably good food, especially their chilaquiles! Homemade hotsauce is tasty as well. A little pricey but worth it.

Fantastic place. Food is out of this world. Staff is kind, helpful, and went out of their way to make sure that we felt at home. My wife and I liked them so much we had them cater our wedding and I am so glad we did. They were were prompt, the food was delicious, the price was unbeatable, and they even laid out everything for us to take home at the end. You can't go wrong with Palo Santo.

(Translated by Google) Customer for nearly ten years from Palo Santo I returned on the occasion of a stay in the US. The restaurant offers reinvented Latin cuisine full of flavors. The wine list is adapted to the dishes and the chef, Jacques Gaultier, will be able to advise you. Fresh market cuisine. Absolutely worth seeing. La carte des vins est adaptée aux plats et le chef, Jacques Gaultier, saura vous conseiller. Cuisine de marché hyper fraîche. Vaut absolument le détour.
Amazing atmosphere, food AND service! Been in this neighborhood 5 years and can’t believe it took us this long to discover this place!
Absolutely fantastic brunch spot, and totally underrated / not too busy. Breakfast tacos are glorious. Cafe con leche is sooooo smooth. I bought some of the hot sauce.
Went here for brunch. Food was good. Service was excellent. They also have a great deal on sangria.
Service was amazing Happy is great Pass on the food
(Translated by Google) It is a special place, full of tradition and good food!  (Original) Es un lugar especial, lleno de tradición y buena comida!
Excellent menu choices . Friendly staff very attentive. Romantic and quiet ambience hidden in the cut of the block.
Great food and experience Prix fixe was definitely worth it

I attended a wedding rehearsal dinner here and we thoroughly enjoyed it. Service was simpatico and laid back. Kind of a rustic feeling. Food was good and abundant -- kind of eclectic Latin style. This little place was a nice find.
Brunch is amazing second mimosa was a dollar when I went. The homemade hot sauce I wanted to steal n take home and I usually don't like hot sauce that much. Staff was awesome as well.
Good food. Pupusas a little big and thick. Nice atmosphere. The waitstaff were great—super friendly!

I came here for Sunday brunch with a couple of friends. It's a super cute little place, nestled in between the buildings. They have one table and a couple of chairs outside- the inside is a little dark, but its big and doesn't feel cramped. The decor is cute! and I love wooden tables and chairs, which is what they have. They also have glittery skull lamps in the window which are cool.  I tried the Prix Fixe which comes with tea/coffee or mimosa/bloody and I had the Huevos Bañados. I highly recommend this, comes on texas toast and all the yummy sauce gets into the bread making it amazing. I will say that the food took time to come to the table, but the service was good, and quick. You get free refills on the coffee and an extra mimosa is $1- great deal!  I will be back for sure

Food was good, however for a party of 20 the waiter shows off about his memory not writing the orders. And everything came wrong. Sauce, meat too much done and he kept blaming the kitchen and giving us free food. Not the kind of service one expects. They charge $1 extra for each credit card, great marketing.
Great Food!!!!+
Tucked away amongst the brownstones and a great little find. Very romantic setting. Fabulous food and good service. Definitely give them a try!
Excellent cozy Mexican restaurant. Wonderful food and service. Reasonable prices. Highly recommend.
Great brunch spot! The prix fixe brunch is great and it’s almost like a bottomless brunch - the first drink is $11 and every refill is just $1. The homemade hot sauce is delicious!

This place exceeded expectations. The food was very tasty, and the location is welcoming. The staff also was super helpful and nice. We had the grass-fed skirt steak and the slow cooked pork. Both were excellent, but the slow cooked pork was just wonderful in every way. Will be back!

This was one of my go to places and I used to visit once a month but something was amiss the last  couple of times I visited. I'm aware of the dynamic nature of the menu but the food just wasn't on par with what I was used to. Perhaps a new chef or kitchen staff? Either way the ambiance is still top notch as is the wait staff. I still recommend choosing from the prix fixe options if it's your first time.
Delicious food. Great service.
The service was great, the food was delicious, I think is a little bit expensive, but it worth it. Great place to have a good diner with somebody.
Friendly staff, good food. Highly recommend the Chilaquiles with their house made hot sauce.

Tasting menu was amazing! The food was amazing and the ambiance was great! Service was a tad slow but if you waved the down they were more than accomodating. Back room is a little cold in the winter but I bet it is enchanting in the summer. Definitely will go back for another special occasion.

Came here for NYE dinner and the service was great and the food was AMAZING. We even ordered late because a couple of us arrived late and although they needed the table for the next reservation, they got our food to us fast and figured out a way to let us stay at the table without making us rush. Best key lime pie and bread pudding I've ever had
Don't miss the tortillas

Love this quaint spot!  The food was hot & tasty!  Best hot sauce I’ve had in a long time.  I wish I would have inquired about purchasing some to go! The only down fall for me was that they don’t have milk alternatives.  Only cow’s milk.  I’m allergic. Otherwise, I’m craving to go back!
Great brunch!
Cute place, food was good and service was attentive.

Cool the restaurant is in the ground floor of a Brownstone. Very cute place with good seating. Small backyard seating is cute and a few patio seating out front. The food was very tasty and good sized portions. Staff was very friendly. Would go back for more!
Excellent food and super nice service. Interesting brunch options, I loved the pork chilaquiles.
Fabulous fresh and delicious! Wonderful combination of flavors and just the right amount of heat. Save room for the bread pudding! Another don't skip are the rabbit tacos.
Cute small Mexican spot

Best rabbit dish I've ever had. And the chimichuri steak is 32 bux, but it tastes likes it's 50 bux. Amazing meat crunchy and tender, with fries that were meant for a giant. Some of the best food I've had in Brooklyn. And they have very special cider too. Delicious.
The brunch as quick, tasty, and decently priced. Good coffee and the chilaquiles with pork were dope.

My cousins had their baby shower here. Soon as you walked in drinks where served to you. The food was great. The shower was from 12pm to 3pm. We had taken over the restaurant for the morning afternoon brunch session. They reopened at 5pm for dinner. The space is not that big. I would say about 16 people could be seat in the front of the restaurant and 26 people people could be seat in the back there is also a very small area of out door seating for maybe 6. There are 2 bathrooms. The staff is very patient, friendly and attentive. My family had a blast. I would totally going again for brunch.
Incredibly delicious. Worth the price in atmosphere and flavor.

Sometimes when restaurants have so many glowing reviews you risk dissappointment because your expectations are so high. But sometimes, like in the case of Palo Santo, those expectations are more than met.  My friend and I had dinner here on Tuesday evening and everything about the experience was lovely. I made a reservation because I know it’s a smaller restaurant (especially when it’s too cold to make use of their outdoor seating) but I believe we wouldn’t have had a problem even if we just walked in, as there were tables available (but it *was* early on a Tuesday).  The restaurant is small and warm and inviting. The service was really good & the staff was also genuine and warm and kind. They have a great happy hour option of a free empanada (or taco) with purchase of an alcoholic drink. My friend ordered a sparkling wine & opted for the beef empanda. I don’t drink, however our server brought me their potato and cheese empanda anyway so we could try both. It was hot and crisp delicious. [Plus their happy hour runs from 6-10pm (M-Th) which is really generous]  I ordered a hearts of palm salad, with avocado pistachios cilantro & mango. It was light and tart and delicious. The portion was also huge. My friend and I shared it & still had enough leftover for both of us to take some home. For my entree I had the fish tacos which were simple and delicous as well. A touch on the saltier side, but nothing that turned me off them. My friend opted for the steak, which was another generous portion. They enjoyed it & I now wish I had tried a bite.  Everyone raves about two things at Palo Santo, the homemade tortillas and the homemade hot sauce. Both were stellar and definitely lived up to the hype. I’d be happy eating both any time.  I had a great evening (with great company which always helps too) and will definitely return!
Good food, slow service. Loud atmosphere. What’s the deal with charging $1 for credit cards??

Tasty food, and a killer happy hour special! We got a free empanada with every drink. Server was very attentive and friendly. Atmosphere was cozy but didn't feel cramped. If I write a few more words I get extra points on Google. Yay! It's worth visiting.

We had a wedding rehearsal luncheon for 30 people. The room at the back is a great space for such event - it was comfortable and private. The food was excellent - great Latin flavors. Gonzalo and the rest of the staff took great care of us and everyone had wonderful time. We definitely will be back.
Very tiny but  cozy place. They have many hearty and delicious dishes! Went there for my birthday. I had a great time. Very friendly staff.
Great hidden gem. Good food and drink selection.
Absolutely delicious!!! Would def recommend the lamb hash.

Really cool neighborhood restaurant, tucked into the middle of a block of brownstones and in a brownstone itself. We had brunch here and it was good across the board. Would love to go back for dinner.
Didn’t get my mind blown. I ve been twice and was not impressed at all given the craze. Maybe I was unlucky twice because they change the menu frequently but not sure I d go back
Environment is chill..pakslope style
Food is good.  Pricey

Nice Latin fusion spot. Brunch options were good and filling without being an overload. They have their own hot sauce that was flavlorful and decently spicy. Atmosphere is great, well done on decor.service was friendly, recluse came along for coffee and water.
Delicious food and great staff!

Yum! I don't usually get sangria at restaurants (I prefer to make my own mix that's not too sweet) but the recipe they have here is on point! The food was fantastic, and so was the bread pudding we got for dessert
Food is amazing service is great
Delicious! Excellent service
Great place the staff was super friendly and the food was wonderful
Consistently excellent. I wish we still lived around the corner! We go back every chance we get .

This is my favorite restaurant in NYC!  There isn't a meal here that isn't excellent, and the space is incredibly charming.  The menu changes frequently, but all of the tacos are incredible no matter what variety.
Fantastic food in a beautiful old brick space.  We loved everything about it.
Amazing ambiance. Great food. Highly recommended.
Delightful food - and really kind, attentive staff!
Great food, super nice staff, cozy, fun.

Love coming to this restaurant for brunch and dinner. Would highly recommend though you should always double check availability because the restaurant is small and they tend to have a lot of private events.

Very small portions of food for a pricey cost. I would not recommend you to go  there if you hungry .After paying a $170 plus tax for 2 skirt steak  order wich had 6 small pieces of the steak and price fix wich I had a banana stew.Food was good But the price is way to high for such a small portion. Ps:The sangria taste like fruit punch no alcohol at all and had lot of old apples (you can tell when they fresh)and too much ice.
The food it’s delicious, and the place lovely of course everybody is super friendly. I love this place

We recently had Palo Santo cater our wedding at The Green Building. Not only were the tacos AMAZING (they made the tortillas fresh on site) but the staff was also so nice and attentive. Gonzalo was a dream to work with leading up to the event and accommodated all of our requests. I can’t recommend Palo Santo enough for your next event!
Great brunch spot that isn’t too busy.  Get a drink with you brunch, and refills are only $1.
Very good South American food! Good environment and nice staff.
Super cozy with amazing cevice!

Great Food! Great Service, Great Prices 😁 #1 We was greeted upon entry with a smile and service, #2 I was served by Green Hair Waitress Quickly and Smoothly, #3 The Food Was Great, #4 The Ambiance was Quaint and Rustic, #5 It Felt like Home...but it wasn't home 😎, #6 We Brought toddler with us without issue, #7 Wonderful changing table, #8 No Rush from Table #9 Waitress checked on us Enough but not too much which was perfect, #10 I will Be Back (Arnold voice)

This place was such an unexpected surprise.  When you walk up it looks like you are going to eat in someone's brownstone.  It was too cold to sit in the garden but I will certainly come back in the summer to check it out.  There were 4 of us - two ordered the tacos, one vegetarian ordered the hearts of palm salad and the other order the duck with mole.   We were all very happy with our dishes.  The handmade tortillas are amazing and my friend is still thinking about his duck dish.  If you like a little spice, you must try the house-made hot sauce.  I still might go back and buy a bottle, it was that good.
Waiting time for the food was a little bit long. Otherwise place was nice and food was good.
Highly recommend the coconut curry!
I wish there was not a table so close to the entrance , although they tried to cover it with the curtains you can still feel the cold. Great food and service.

Great, cozy atmosphere. Tasty food: tacos, avocado, coconut stew aspragus, swordfish. Love mate - favorite. With cactus sorbet and tres leches, great company of friends - what could be better on a Sunday evening night.
Our server was amazing!
I came here with my mom after seeing some great reviews but I'm a bit disappointed with the food. It was decent at best and overpriced for its portion size.
Great food, great service. Will def come back.
The food here is amazing! Very cute, quaint atmosphere.. would definitely come back!
Went there with a friend from out of town, great brunch spot. Service was outstanding. They didn't rush us, let us have time catch up, and food was delicious. Would recommend for anyone on a Sunday.
The food and the staff are amazing
Really good! The pre fix menu is a great deal and taco happy hour is fab. My entree was a lil salty, but like everything was delicious.
Atomosphere, food and staff all excellent. Definitely go
Good food, too expensive.

Secretly my favorite low key brunch place in the slope.  Distinct dishes, friendly and accommodating staff, cool furniture and laid back vibe.  Snagging the two outdoor seats in the front on a sunny day are a clutch move.
Nice place and good food
Limited menbut good food
Delicious food and the servers are really attentive!

Miserable experience. We were one of two parties at the spot for brunch. Our food took an hour and a half to arrive because the kitchen lost our ticket and nobody noticed. 1 cup of coffee and a very small portion of over salted pumpkin soup cost $25
The chilaquiles for brunch delicious! I do wish the portion was bigger and there was a bit more egg, but the food and drinks were all very good.

Horrible experience Jack the owner was rude and hung up the phone on me. The staff( Gonzalo was rude to me). They refused to refund a deposit. Place small crowed and overpriced. Bad service! #boycottpalosanto

We found Palo Santo while googling taco bar catering for our wedding and it was the cutest restaurant with the best deal we could find. The wedding was last weekend and I just had to say that everyone was blown away by the quality and service. The tacos were delicious (even the vegan option), came with an abundance of sides and toppings, and the on site pressed tortillas made the experience unique and super fresh. Everyone had plenty to eat and we had so many compliments on the food. We will definitely be going out of our way to visit the restaurant often!

The atmosphere was great, the staff was excellent and the wine absolutely wonderful. I had a great time during the wine pairing. We had 3 different dishes and dessert. I tried rabbit ravioli and it actually tasted good. The steak was to die for. Everything was perfect.
It is very warm and cozy restaurant. Unfortunately the back was reserved but still we enjoyed our time and food over there.
Omfg we've been here for 1.5 hours waiting for tacos and a salad! So freaking angry!!!
Rounded find from 4.5.  Good food and service but slightly pricy for what you get
Amazing food.  I've never had a bad meal here. Nice atmosphere. Never too crowded and even kid friendly.  Can't go wrong whether it's date night or you are with a big group.
Great place for brunch! The French toast is really good and different. Adorable setting and great service. Defiantly going back.
Food was very unappetizing and had not much flavor. The ambiance was very nice and had a good vibe.
Skirt steak and gazpacho were FANTASTIC.
Great food and service!
Excellent food, friendly service. There was a large party in the back which delayed our food coming out, but otherwise a great experience.
My daughter had her baby shower there, and we were happy about the food, service and price.

The food here is amazing--always interesting and always well-done. Space is lovely, and awesomely funky. Sangria is delish!
Great space and great food.
Good quality. Poor service. I find it expensive for casual food.
Great coffee, the Prix fixe menu is full of tough choices.
The steak was amazing
not bad a little boring.

Seasonal menu with decent latin food. I'm disappointed in the variety and prices for such a casual place. They have decent sangria, but not a full service bar. The avocado tacos and organ meat are both good.

My best friend's rehearsal dinner was here and we experienced fabulous Latin faire and a wonderful staff. The "whole" shrimp and mini tostados are an absolute must along with their hibiscus cocktails.

Wonderful intimate space with excellent food and outstanding service. Held a bridal shower brunch here and had a really great experience all around. They couldn't have done anything more to exceed our expectations. Highly recommend dining here and absolutely recommend considering them for your next organized event! Special thank you to Gonzalo and his friendly staff for accommodating us like family

(Translated by Google) An ordinary American Mexican. The shopkeeper is gay. Like other stores, wine is unusually expensive. I would like the list to be a little cheaper.  (Original) 普通のアメリカン・メキシカン。店主はゲイですね。他の店もそうでしたが、ワインが異常に高い。もう少し安いラインからのリストにしてほしいです。
Food is correct but portions are really small for brunch. The place is cozy and the service is fast and attentive.
Food and the one drink someone at our table got was excellent. Small but cozy setting. They make nice use of the space.
Romantic atmosphere and friendly service.  Try the lamb shank...so tasty.

We had our daughter's first birthday party at Palo Santo last weekend and it was great! The guests loved the food, the ambience and them allowing us to decorate the place! Gonzalo and team were very accommodating when we dropped the cake off before hand and when we wanted to change up the style of how we wanted the food served. Highly recommended for parties of 20-25 people.
Really interesting restaurant. Very cozy. Great for a date and be food is pretty good too
Had a lovely meal here. Wonderful service in a warm homey setting.  Also great cocktails.
Fantastic ambiance, service, and food. Try everything! Can't believe I missed this place before now. It's hidden in the middle of a residential street.
My Wedding Reception was amazing in this place in 2013.
Great little place to have a party. Lots of Spanish cuisine
Awesome
Nice place. Charming, not too busy on Friday night. A little on the pricey side for the quality and quantity of food you get. Enjoyable experience overall.

Venue is inviting and it's great that you can sit at the bar to watch the chef's do their thing. 3 course prix fixe menu was outstanding value and equally scrumptious. Service spot on that is fast friendly and efficient.
Really solid food in a quirky brownstone building.  Good for dinner, but I love it for brunch.  It's usually not too crazy for brunch and the prices are very reasonable.
Good food, fun, nice date / brunch spot

Went for dinner on a Saturday with my wife.  Place was fairly full but not crowded.  Took a very long time to get approached by our server, then a very long time between courses and dessert.  Not sure if they were understaffed tonight or it's a sign of the deterioration of an otherwise great restaurant.  The food was very good but with the poor service and very long wait, I don't think we'll be back.
Great food I went there for a brunch so good.The toast , rice, chicken,
Great place one of a kind!!
The menu is always fresh and seasonal, the dishes are inventive and flavorful, totally unique... one of my favorites in Park Slope!
The experience here is awesome 🍷🍻
Menu and service average. Limited beverage selection. Expensive relative to wrinkled menus, wobbly table, threadbare banquettes.

This is the second time I visit this restaurant. The first time I thought the food was just ok, but the service was terrible.  At my spouse's insistence, we went back yesterday. The service was terrible beyond belief. We were sat at a table near the door, and then asked to move to another table to accommodate other patrons. We agreed and were generously offered a glass of sparkling sangria.  We placed our order and waited for 50 minutes. During that wait time, we didn't get utensils or dishes. When we asked our waiter why we weren't getting utensils, he sneered. When we called the maitre to ask about our food, we were invited to leave if we couldn't be patient. We were very polite about the whole thing and left.  Must say, why come to this restaurant to be mistreated?  There are many good restaurants in Park Slope with better service.
This food here was magnificent!!! We stopped in for a quick dinner and we would definitely come back.  You must try it if you are in the area.  Service was exceptional!

Really nice restaurant experience. Its a nice cosy spot, and it really captures the vibe of an authentic latin restaurant.  The food was excellent and I really liked that they had a prix fix option for $33 which include a starter, main and desert. Not all mains were included but this was still reasonable value.  I would really recommend this place for a sit down meal when you are not in a rush, it has a relaxing atmosphere and time passes by fast.
Nice place and good food ! Went there for a brunch and it was very good !
Cozy restaurant with delicious food. The tuna was delicious but size could be a little bit larger. Excellent spicy sangria

This past October, my parents planned a baby shower for my better half in the back room of Palo Santo and every guest was amazed with the level of professionalism, care, cuisine and great service provided by the staff. Gonzalo is a gem and so is every aspect of this restaurant.  We will be coming back for more delicious pulled pork sandwiches, the plantain stew and a welcoming smile from the staff. Yum, yum

I found the ceviche to be excellent and other dishes good, but the portions were small and the prices high for what you received. No service problems, but the price to benefit (quality and quantity) ratio was off. Probably would not return.
loved it. I had my mothers birthday party here for 20 people and it was a successes. food was great, service good if not superb and we had fun, fun, fun.
Great food. Great service! Jackie and her boyfriend were the best!

Palo Santo is a quaint taco restaurant with wooden chairs and tables, funky hardware for the door handles, and an old fashioned pedal-operated sink in the bathroom. Stick to the regular tacos such as the beef, pork and chicken. They have others like cactus, but it was not popular with my group. Beer is served in pitchers as well. Attentive waitstaff, save room for dessert.

Delicious brunch!!  With all the options available in Park Slope this was a surprising find.  The food was traditional brunch items with Spanish flavors.  From Pina Colada French Toast to an Avocado and cheese omlette, it was all so yummy.  Entrees come with sangria or mimosa and if you want a second, it's just $1.  The best deal in BK!
Awesome hidden gem

I’ve been try to explore the culinary establishments of Brooklyn and Park Slope neighborhood. Along to streets of tacos. We went here for Sunday Brunch. The interior is quaint with wood and comfortable and plenty of locals. The host was friendly as was the server.  The brunch menu was limited but enough selection to make everyone happy. We had the Bluefish Ceviche, Papaya salad and the egg/bacon sandwich. The ceviche was quite good. Great flavors and the papaya was firm and sweet with the slightly spicy watercrest. The egg/bacon sandwich was what it was but equally as good served with yucca fries and spicy mayo dipping sauce.  We certainly enjoy the meal and looking at the dinner menu, it looked just as good. But the let down was for the price and amount it left us wanting a little bit more in way of portions.

Palo Santo has something for everyone, from Latin-twists on comfort food to more adventurous choices like rabbit. They put a lot of care into making food from scratch here, whipping cream by hand, toasting spices for 2 days for mole, chopping herbs by hand for chimichurri, etc. A great gem for the neighborhood.

I was fortunate to find this hidden gem in Park Slope. I was looking for an intimate space for my July wedding and came across Palo Santo! I noticed  on their website the opportunity to rent half the space or the entire venue. The pictures of palo santo on their website do not do any justice compared to visiting the space. I felt in love with the intimate feel of the brick wall and the nostalgic pieces hung around the venue. The space transforms from the day to a bright open space with the natural lighting and at night the lights are dim to give a romantic feel. The food is adjusted on a daily basis. You cannot go wrong with any item on the menu.  It has been nearly a year since my wedding and our friends and family are still mentioning how memorable the food, service and the environment was. I highly recommend Palo Santo for any events or simply to enjoy a great meal.

It's *very* hard to find something bad to say about Palo Santo. It's located in the bottom floor of a brownstone which by itself is pretty cool. Great ambiance, big space in back, very romantic and dimly lit with a rustic Latin vibe. Had tons of fun here both on a date and with a small group of friends.  The food is more adventurous, experimental, and different than most other restaurants in the Slope so do yourself a favor and look at the menu before you go to see if it suits your appetite.  They have a single table for the outdoor seating in their uber small backyard, but for what it is it's done extremely well.

Palo Santo hosted an anniversary celebration in the back room. Staff did an excellent job. Food on a fixed menu was good. Pupusas were probably the best dish, but we only tasted that because one of us found some wire from a Brillo pad in her food and the staff comped us. Chicken and pork were just all right. Beans and avo to start were tasty. Ask for their house hot sauce - it's excellent.
Excellent Prix Fixe Brunch for $15! If you ask nicely, they might give you a free refill of Mimosa!
I have been coming here since 2006. The quality of the food is always amazing. We had two new years celebration and their taste for matching food with wine is great too.
Excellent Food, nice quiet location and the service was very friendly. I'll definitely be going back!

Fantastic ingredients, terrible service. Best known for use of local, sustainably-raised in-season ingredients. The chef doesn't use anything processed at all- he uses animal fat from pastured animals for cooking and makes his own stocks and tortillas! Very unusual in the restaurant business. Unfortunately this restaurant is almost always understaffed, leading to a harried and frustrating dining experience.

I find I enjoy the "simpler" items on the menu more -- conch chowder, beans and rice, and other simple dishes seems to have wonderfully complex flavors. Plus, they're quite a bit more of a bargain than the larger cuts of meat. Brunch is fantastic. If you're splurging, go for the 15-course tasting menu (you'll have to sit at the bar). A few years ago it was an incredible bargain and even better experience at $50 (plus $40 wine pairings). Overall a great restaurant and I'd argue that it is closer to $$ than the $$$ that the magazine lists.  I'm surprised at the comments about service, as I've eaten here about a half-dozen times over the years and the chef/owner has been nothing but wonderfully friendly. Hope those incidents were just flukes or misunderstandings.
they cater brooklyn soda which is made in the basement.

This is the type of food that New Yorkers love. It's well made, in a comfortable atmosphere, and completely overpriced. My girlfriend and I ordered the ceviche and each got two small bites of soupy fish and few sprigs of celantro for $14. This was, by far, the most expensive ceviche I've ever eaten, and no where near the best. I've never had my ceviche swimming in the marinade sauce, which was  probably supposed to fill-out the dish and make it look larger. It was really pathetic. If you want to get some great food for a good price, this is a poor choice.
frere jacques...our brother in the kitchen! always a flavor extravaganza with south american wines. the avocado creme brulee is unbelievably sublime -- a top ten dessert.
